==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from Hindi qūlī, which means "hired laborer." Other forms occur in the Bengali, ''kuli'' and the Tamil, ''kuli'', "daily hire." Maybe related to the Chinese word [[苦]][[力]] ([[Pinyin]]: kǔlì)

=== Noun ===
'''coolie''' (or '''cooly''')
# an [[unskilled]] [[Asian]] [[worker]], usually of [[Chinese]] or [[Inidan]] descent; a labourer; a porter.

[[Category:Hindi derivations]]
[[Category:Chinese derivations]]
# name of a flavored slush drink sold at "Cum and Go" convience stores
# in [[Trinidad]], West Indies, Guayana, Africa [[slang]] for a person of [[Indian]] descent. Nowadays sometimes derogatory.

